cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR

This paper is about person re-identification (ReID) using neural networks, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an end-to-end fully convolutional Siamese network, which involves training deep neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses spatial transformer networks (STNs) and proposes an improved ranking loss, which are techniques commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research, respectively. Finally, the paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed method, which is a topic often studied in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
